<abstract>
<t>This memo describes a new IPv6 Hop-by-Hop Option type that alerts transit routers to more closely examine the contents of an IP datagram.  This option is useful for situations where a datagram  addressed to a particular destination contains information that may require special processing by routers along the path.</t></abstract></front>

